^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Some pairs play the Lebensohl convention after partner makes a takeout double of a weak 2-bid. That means with a weak hand, responder bids 2N as a conventional bid. That forces the doubler to bid 3@C. Responder passes with clubs or corrects to his suit. That sequence shows a weak hand (no more than 7 or perhaps a bad 8 and usually less). If you play that, then an immedate 3 level bid by responder (such as what happened on this hand), shows an invitational hand.|
